Variables:
 Are like boxes/containers which can hold data for us.We can change the data
 later on if we want. We can reuse the same variables as many times as we
 want. There are 8 basic/primitive data types.
 Four basic data types to store whole numbers.
1)byte 2)short 3)int 4)long
 2 basic data types to store decimal numbers
1)float 2)double
 1 data type
 to store characters:
   char
 To Store true/false
   boolean
 Non Primitives:
  1) String
